# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Track ONLY the news/ folder (and this .gitignore).
# Everything else lives on disk and is deployed via rsync, but is no
# longer part of the GitHub repo. The "/*" pattern is root-anchored,
# so it ignores top-level entries only — files INSIDE news/ are not
# affected by it and remain tracked.
# Reminder: this only affects new files. Already-tracked files stay
# in the index until removed with `git rm --cached`.
# -------------------------------------------------------------------
/*
!/news/
!/.gitignore

# The news page HTML shell is served by nest, not fetched from GitHub —
# only news/*.md and image assets are runtime-relevant.
/news/index.html

# Also track /assets/images/ (image assets referenced from elsewhere).
# Un-ignore the assets/ parent first (gitignore can't re-include a file
# under an ignored parent), then re-ignore everything one level under
# assets/, then re-include just assets/images/.
!/assets/
/assets/*
!/assets/images/